                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/872: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-15T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 15, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 15—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Preparatory Commission met this morning and after president had made rather
                    innocuous speech he submitted a proposed agenda which is substantially the
                    Colban proposal slightly elaborated.</p>
                <p>This will be discussed at tomorrow morning’s meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
